2026-03-30 22:07:13,165 | INFO | readme_agent_api | [AGENT] Tool call: {'tool': 'create_or_update_file', 'input': {'branch': 'main', 'path': 'README.md', 'message': 'docs: add README generated by readme-agent', 'repo': 'codecreator', 'content': '# CodeCreator\n\n> A modular Flask web application for orchestrating agent calls, API endpoints, and function packages.\n\n## 🧠 Overview\n\nThis project is a Flask web application designed to provide a structured and modular foundation for various functionalities. It handles the initial setup, configuration, and registration of different application modules, allowing for clear separation of concerns and extensibility.\n\n## 🔨 What I Built\n\nThe core of CodeCreator is a Flask application factory that ensures proper initialization and configuration. Key features include:\n- **Modular Architecture:** Utilizes Flask Blueprints to organize agent calls, API endpoints, and function packages into distinct modules.\n- **Application Configuration:** Centralized setup of the Flask application instance.\n- **Extension Initialization:** Integration point for Flask extensions.\n\n## 💭 Thought Process\n\nThe design prioritizes modularity and clear separation of concerns. By using an application factory pattern and Flask Blueprints, the project aims to create a scalable and maintainable structure where different functionalities (agent calls, API, functions) can be developed and managed independently while being integrated seamlessly into the main application.\n\n## 🛠️ Tools & Tech Stack\n\n| Layer     | Technology |\n|-----------|------------|\n| Framework | Flask      |\n\n## 🚀 Getting Started\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Python 3.x\n\n### Installation\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/rashadmin/codecreator.git\ncd codecreator\npip install Flask\n```\n\n### Run\n\n```bash\nexport FLASK_APP=app\nflask run\n```\n\n## 📖 Usage\n\n### API Usage\n\n```\n# Example: Sending a request to a hypothetical agent endpoint\n# (Actual endpoint and payload would depend on specific blueprint implementations)\ncurl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d \'{"prompt": "generate python code for a given task"}\' http://localhost:5000/agent/generate\n```\n\n## 📚 Resources\n\n- [Flask Documentation](https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/latest/)\n\n## 📄 License\n\nMIT © [rashadmin](https://github.com/rashadmin)\n', 'owner': 'rashadmin'}}
